mx.org.pescadormvp.core.client.placesandactivities

Interface PAVComponent<I extends PAVComponent<I,P>,P extends PescadorMVPPlace>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - The component's public interface.
    P - The place class associated with this component.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Component<I>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    QueryComponent
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PAVComponentBase, QueryComponentImpl

    public interface PAVComponent<I extends PAVComponent<I,P>,P extends PescadorMVPPlace>
extends Component<I>
    A place-activity-view component. A special kind of component that associates a place class with activity classes, view classes and regions of the UI.

    • Method Detail

      • getRawPlace

        P getRawPlace()
        Get a new place of the class associated with this PAVComponent. This place normally won't have any extra info, URL, presentation text or any other stuff yet.

      • handlesRegions

      • getActivity

        <A extends PescadorMVPPlaceActivity<?,P,?>> A getActivity(Class<? extends ForRegionTag> region,
                                                        P place)
        Internal Pescador MVP use. Get a new activity for the region specified, and provide it with the place specified.
        Parameters:
        region - The UI region for which you want a new activity.
        place - The place that this activity will use (accessible from the within the activity via getPlace()).
        Returns:
        The new activity.

      • ensureSessionData

        <S extends SessionData> S ensureSessionData()
        Get this PAVComponent's SessionData. (And if it hasn't been created yet, create it first.)

      • finalizeSetup

        void finalizeSetup()
        Called by GlobalSetup on components once all components have been registered. Don't call it yourself, just implement it to do stuff that can only be done once all components are registered, or leave it empty if your component has nothing to do at that time. Note: PAVComponentBase provides a default empty implementation.
        Specified by:
        finalizeSetup in interface Component<I extends PAVComponent<I,P>>
